 families who have money...who is going to care about education and &quot;rise up to make changes to the system&quot; when the only worries nowadays is our own well being. Who cares about the others? we already go to church every sunday and have the money to donate to some random charity, so why worrying about THE EDUCATION of others.   Individualism is part of our society. From the 2 or 3 years ive been living in this country, you dont know how many times ive heard &quot;survival of the fittest&quot; or something related to social darwinism to approve the way our society works. If someone asks me what is going to happen first between waiting for people with money to &quot;rise up to make changes to the system&quot; and waiting for cows to fly...i would say i trust on cows... "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1064" language="en" documentId="3443" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="DaveGL" date="Aug 29, 2013 7:11PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="4" thumbsDown="0" origId="3443" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1064"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>